programme.title: Live PGA Tour Golf
programme.desc: The CJ Cup. Coverage of day one of the second staging of the tournament, held at the Club at Nine Bridges on Jeju Island in South Korea. Justin Thomas prevailed at the inaugural staging of the event last year, beating Marc Leishman in a play-off after the two finished level on an overall score of nine-under par. While the American is not expected to be in attendance this year, the field will include a number of star names such as Paul Casey, Jason Day, Tony Finau, Tyrrel Hatton and Brooks Koepka.(n)

programme.title: Live European Tour Golf
programme.sub-title: 2018 Andalucia Valderrama Masters: Day One - Session One
programme.desc: The Andalucia Valderrama Masters. Coverage of the opening day of the tournament from the Real Club Valderrama in Sotogrande, southern Spain, hosted by the Sergio Garcia Foundation. Garcia himself took the honours last year, finishing one stroke clear of Joost Luitten to win his third title of 2018. The home favourite will go into the tournament this time around with confidence, having recently broken the all-time record for Ryder Cup points.(n)
